Sentencas: Poor durability is one of the major hurdles for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) commercialization.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: Prognostic technology is an important approach to improve system durability.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: However, the current prognostic methods for fuel cells are mainly applied to proton exchange membrane fuel cell (PEMFC) systems, moreover, there are still shortages of recent prognostic algorithms.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: Therefore, an improved prognostic model is developed to predict the remaining useful life of the SOFC in this study, which combines a hidden semi-Mark model (HSMM) with an empirical model.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: To build the hybrid prognostic model, an HSMM and an empirical model are firstly built.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: The merit and demerit of the respective prognostic methodology are then analyzed.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: According to the analysis results, the hybrid prognostic model is proposed and applied to six sets of SOFC run-to-failure data.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics

Sentencas: The results show the proposed prognostic model has a higher prediction accuracy and a faster forecasting speed compared with the existed approaches for SOFC prognostics.
Titulo: A hybrid prognostic model applied to SOFC prognostics
